Downstream Effects

Both models are predicting the downstream effect of having a conversation with the target.

With BFI

Model output to pull coeffs

bfi_stereo <- lmer(bfi_targ_pmc ~ bfi_self_pmc*itt_comp_gmc*target_condition*bfi_stereo_pmc +
                     (bfi_self_pmc + bfi_stereo_pmc | sub_id), data = bfi_data)

Getting coefficients

mod_coeffs <-coefficients(bfi_stereo)

cp_main <- mod_coeffs$sub_id$bfi_self_pmc
threat_comp <- mod_coeffs$sub_id$`bfi_self_pmc:itt_comp_gmc`
threat_targ_loss <- mod_coeffs$sub_id$`bfi_self_pmc:target_conditionLOSS`
threat_targ_warm <- mod_coeffs$sub_id$`bfi_self_pmc:target_conditionWARM`
int_warm_cont <- mod_coeffs$sub_id$`bfi_self_pmc:itt_comp_gmc:target_conditionWARM`
int_loss_cont <- mod_coeffs$sub_id$`bfi_self_pmc:itt_comp_gmc:target_conditionLOSS`
sub_id <- bfi_data %>% 
  select(sub_id, will_to_convo) %>% 
  unique()

coeffs_df <- cbind(sub_id, cp_main, threat_comp, threat_targ_loss, threat_targ_warm,
                   int_warm_cont, int_loss_cont)

coeffs_df %<>% 
  mutate(will_to_convo = as.numeric(dplyr::recode(will_to_convo,
                       `0 minutes` = "1",
                       `15 minutes` = "2",
                       `30 minutes` = "3",
                       `45 minutes` = "4",
                       `60 minutes` = "5")))

Models predicting downstream

Main Effect

# Singularities with so many in the models, so will do individual models
downstream_main <- lm(will_to_convo ~ cp_main, data = coeffs_df)

Visualization

  geom_smooth(method = "lm",
              colour = "black") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13) +
    theme(legend.key.size = unit(1, "cm")) +
  labs(title = "Projection coefficients using BFI predicting behavior with target",
         subtitle = "Negative coefficients indicate counter-projection",
       y = "Time willing to converse (1 = None; 5 = 60 Minutes)",
       x = "Projection coefficients (BFI)")

With ELI

Model (from ELI test of residual counter-projection)

eli_data <- clean_data_eli %>% 
  select(sub_id, eli_number, eli_targ_pmc, eli_self_pmc, itt_comp_gmc,
         target_condition, eli_targ, eli_self, eli_stereo, eli_stereo_pmc,
         analog_condition, itt_comp, will_to_convo) %>% 
  unique() %>% 
  na.omit() 

eli_mod<- lmer(eli_targ_pmc ~ eli_self_pmc*itt_comp_gmc*eli_stereo_pmc + # itt does not work as a RE; model does not converge
                     (0 + eli_self_pmc + eli_stereo_pmc | sub_id), 
                   data = eli_data)
summary(eli_mod)

  select(sub_id, will_to_convo) %>% 
  unique()

coeffs_df_eli <- cbind(sub_id_eli, cp_main_eli, threat_comp_eli)
